Carta will̃mi filii wil̃l̃i mauꝑcii de terra in wymbyfl̃ in ꝑochia de Thaxstede
m̃ib ⁊c̃ Will̃ms filius Will̃i mauꝑcus sal̃tm Nou̾it uniu̾sitasͧ ͬmͣe dedisse ⁊ concessisse ⁊ hac
p̾senti carta mea confirmasse deo ⁊ beate marie ⁊ domui fr̾m hospitl̃is sc̃i Iohis Ierl̃m ꝓ salute aĩe mee
⁊ añcessoꝵ ⁊ succ̃ meoꝵ totam t̾ram quam Ric̃us filius Mich̃is de Wymb̃ in Serdeleia in ꝑochia de
Thaxsted̃ de me tenuit cũ homagiis ⁊ seruic̃ ⁊ om̃ib lib̃tatib in siluis in uiis in semitis h̃end̃ ⁊ tenend̃
de me ⁊ hered̃ meis dc̃is frĩb dc̃i hospitl̃is in lib̃am puram ⁊ ꝑpetuam elemosinã ita pure ⁊ lib̃e sicut
aliqua elemosina purius ⁊ lib̃ius dari potest Ego uero Will̃ms ⁊ hered̃ mei warantizabimus p̾dc̃am
t̾ram p̾dc̃is frĩb cũ homagiis ⁊ redditib ⁊ cet̾is lib̃tatib ut nr̃am lib̃am puram ⁊ ꝑpetuam elemosinã
contra om̃es homĩes ⁊ feĩas Et uc hec mea donacio ⁊ concessio ⁊ carte mee confirmacio ⁊ warantizacio
rata ⁊ stabilis ꝑseu̾et p̾sens scriptũ sigilli mei apposicione roboram hiis testib ⁊c̃.|
Carta Ioh̃nis Coci de Dunmawe de undecim denariis redditꝰ in villa de Dunmawe
m̃ib ⁊c̃. Ioh̃nes Cocus de Dunmawe sal̃tm Nou̾itis me dedisse ⁊ concessisse ⁊ p̾senti scripto con
firmasse ꝓ salute aĩe mee ⁊ añcessoꝵ ⁊ succ̃ meoꝵ deo ⁊ beate marie ⁊ frĩb hospitl̃is sc̃i Ioh̃is Ierl̃m in
libam puram ⁊ ꝑpetuam elemosinam xi denar̃ annui reddit̃ quos Radũs Cole michi annuatim reddere
cousueuit ad duos anni t̾mĩos scil̃it ad Pascha quĩq denar̃ ⁊ ob̃l̃m ⁊ ad fm̃ sc̃i Mich̃is quĩq denarios
⁊ ob̃ ꝓ duab acris t̾re arabilis ⁊ una acra prati quas tenuit de me in uilla de Dunmawe magna
cũ ꝑtĩn suis quaꝵ una acra t̾re iacet in campo qui uocat᷑ Stratford̃ int̃ t̾ram Ioh̃is de la fford̃ ⁊ t̾rã
Galfr̃ filii Rob̃ti snecte ⁊ abuttat ad unũ capud̃ suꝑ t̾ram Gilb̃ti Drapier ⁊ ad aliud suꝑ le hol̃m ⁊ una
roda prati iacet in monemãnemad̃ ⁊ alia acra t̾re iacet in campo p̾noĩat̃ int̃ t̾ram Arnulfi de fraxino
⁊ t̾ram p̾dc̃i Ioh̃is de la ford̃ ⁊ extendit se t̾ra p̾fat̃ Gilb̃ti usq ad ripam ⁊ tres rode prati iacent in
mone mãnemad̃ cũ toto homagio ⁊ seruic̃ dc̃i Radĩ ⁊ cũ om̃ib ꝑtĩn ⁊ lib̃tatib ⁊ aisiam̃et̃ a p̾dc̃am t̾rã
spectantib h̃end̃ ⁊ tenend̃ dc̃is fr̾ib lib̃e ⁊ pure ⁊ quiet̃ ⁊ inꝑp̃m solut̃ ⁊ quiet̃ ab om̃ib scl̃arib seruic̃
⁊ querelis ⁊ demand̃ uidel̃it ita lib̃e ⁊ quiet̃ sicut aliqua elemosina lib̃ius ⁊ purius ab aliquo pot̾it
dari uel recipi Ego uero Ioh̃nes cocus ⁊ hered̃ mei warantizabimus p̾noĩat̃ teñ cũ om̃ib ꝑtĩn
suis p̾fat̃ fr̾ib sicut nr̃am lib̃am puram ⁊ ꝑpetuam elemosinam contra om̃es homĩes ⁊ feĩas Et
quia uolo qd̶ hec mea donacio ⁊ concessio ⁊ confirmacio ⁊ warantizacio rata ⁊ stabilis inꝑp̃m ꝑseu̾et

ĩn eadm̃ villa de dunmawe
Om̃ib ⁊c̃ Ioh̃nes Cocus salutem Nou̾it uniu̾sitas ⁊c̃ me dedisse ⁊ concessise ⁊ p̾senti scripto confir
masse ꝓ salute aĩe mee ⁊ añcessoꝵ ⁊ succ̃ meoꝵ deo ⁊ beati marie ⁊ fr̾ib hospit̃ sc̃i Ioh̃is Ierl̃m octo
denarios annui reddit̃ cũ ꝑtĩn quos saiectus Carpentarius michi reddere cousueuit ꝓ trib acris tr̾e
⁊ una roda quas de me tenuit in uilla de Dunmawe magna in lib̃am puram ⁊ ꝑpetuã elemosinã
⁊ maxime domui ip̃oꝵ fr̃m de Chaur̃ h̃end̃ ⁊ tenend̃ dc̃is fr̾ib de me ⁊ hered̃ meis ita lib̃e ⁊ quiet̃
ꝓut aliqua elemosina pot̾it ab aliquo dari uel recipi Ego vero Cocus ⁊ herered̃ mei warantiza
bimus p̾noĩat̃ redditũ cũ ꝑtĩn p̾dc̃is fr̾ib sicut nr̃am lib̃am purã ⁊ ꝑpetuã elemosinam contra
¶ Chaureth.
